{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:17:41.872860+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 98, "prompt_tokens": 8439, "total_tokens": 8537, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 7, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8064}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8064, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 375}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "51e3b83b-f704-4bee-b6f6-c3e0ffb29f49", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f2-d08b-79e3-ae9a-f0bf039f650e-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02", "path": "docs/algorithm.md"}, "id": "call_00_cwqu4Izw6hyGIX8vTMox4867", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8439, "output_tokens": 98, "total_tokens": 8537, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8064}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 7}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:17:42.698850+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 819eb66d8fc6d3b07867d7e86e545cfb4d1a53d3)", "id": "lc_b3bb6613-f01f-48d3-90de-c263d1ce1867"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Algorithm: token bucket\n\nEach bucket has two parameters set at construction:\n\n- `capacity`: maximum tokens in the bucket\n- `refill_per_sec`: tokens regenerated per real second, capped at `capacity`\n\nOn each `check(key, cost=1)` call:\n\n1. Read `tokens` and `ts` (timestamp of last update) from the bucket.\n2. Compute `tokens += (now - ts) * refill_per_sec`, capped at `capacity`.\n3. If `tokens >= cost`, decrement and return `(allowed=True, remaining)`.\n4. Otherwise, leave `tokens` unchanged and return `(allowed=False, remaining)`.\n5. Persist `tokens` and `ts = now`.\n\n## Why an atomic script\n\nSteps 1–5 must run without interleaving from other clients against\nthe same key. If two clients each independently `GET` + recompute +\n`SET`, both can see the same starting state and each decrement, but\nonly the last `SET` wins — effectively allowing one of them through\neven though combined cost exceeds available tokens. Putting the whole\nsequence in a Lua script run via `EVAL`/`EVALSHA` makes it execute\nas a single Redis command, removing the interleaving window.\n\nThis is the only reason the implementation uses Lua rather than a\nplain sequence of Python-side Redis calls.\n", "id": "lc_bfb40ecf-2641-4120-aecf-e608607faebc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b1bd5ccd-e6dc-42c6-82e9-f6dd3dbf77a9", "tool_call_id": "call_00_cwqu4Izw6hyGIX8vTMox4867", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:17:49.637409+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 523, "prompt_tokens": 8880, "total_tokens": 9403, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 431, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8448}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8448, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 432}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "d2b8ad8d-ffc1-44ec-9e5a-089fd5c9bcd6", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f2-dbac-7dc0-aa32-07c8c36a493f-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02", "path": "CHANGELOG.md"}, "id": "call_00_wy3QTLq106P0YzdetTCx6576", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8880, "output_tokens": 523, "total_tokens": 9403, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8448}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 431}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:17:50.422966+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6791d30657fac06c3de5da7d6ecb5e6d11e3435d)", "id": "lc_96adc408-d29a-48ab-9334-2bf49f645fd1"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Changelog\n\n## [0.2.0] - 2025-04-30\n\n### Fixed\n- `examples/flask_app.py`: replaced ambiguous `refill_per_sec=10/60`\n  with a leaky-bucket-style configuration so the demo enforces a hard\n  10/min cap. The library remains a continuous-refill token bucket;\n  the example now matches the README's \"10 requests per minute\" copy.\n- README: clarified the difference between burst-allowed token bucket\n  semantics and strict-cap leaky bucket semantics in the API\n  walkthrough.\n\n### Library behavior\n\nNo changes to `bucket.lua` or `Limiter.check()`. The library is\nunchanged in 0.2.0 — only the example and doc copy. Existing users\ndo not need to migrate.\n\n## [0.1.0] - 2025-03-15\n\n### Added\n- Initial release: `Limiter`, `bucket.lua` (atomic token bucket),\n  Flask demo.\n", "id": "lc_5e29e734-2bda-463b-a0dd-30444fd5954e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4f76080b-fb2d-4d2d-811a-fff4dc1fc5e0", "tool_call_id": "call_00_wy3QTLq106P0YzdetTCx6576", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
