{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:17:54.539141+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: bb0338cf544d7eee70668d033fbe48b8a40e3355)", "id": "lc_6af16883-6241-4f56-a451-349051dc5ec5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"ratelimit-redis\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\ndescription = \"Redis-backed token-bucket rate limiter\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nlicense = { text = \"MIT\" }\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\"redis>=5.0\"]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nexamples = [\"flask>=3.0\"]\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\"src\"]\n", "id": "lc_1dccb801-f1b9-4eca-86dc-65e074c4e114"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ae7d6909-c08b-40d3-96c8-e8afef319ad0", "tool_call_id": "call_00_DBWIuTlqJTQTfF0FtHSS8572", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:18:07.508703+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1156, "prompt_tokens": 10094, "total_tokens": 11250, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 737, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9856}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 9856, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 238}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "bf8e93cf-0605-4cf4-a76f-4451de773420", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f3-09eb-7930-8f97-412f531a122b-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the detailed report, @BruceKZ. You've correctly identified the root cause: the algorithm itself (`bucket.lua`) is a standard **token bucket** and is working as intended. The bucket starts full (`capacity=10`), so the first 10 requests are served immediately, and during that burst (and over the remaining minute), tokens refill at `10/60` per second — giving you roughly 20 requests in the first 60 seconds. After that initial drain, the steady-state rate settles to ~10/min.\n\nThe problem is the **example configuration and its comment** — it claims \"rate-limit a Flask endpoint to 10 requests per minute per IP,\" but a token bucket with `capacity=10` and `refill_per_sec=10/60` does *not* enforce a hard 10/min ceiling; it enforces an *average* of 10/min with bursts up to 10 at once.\n\nThe `CHANGELOG.md` already acknowledges this and describes the intended fix for the next release:\n- Update `examples/flask_app.py` to use a leaky-bucket-style configuration (e.g., `capacity=1`, `refill_per_sec=10/60`) so the demo truly caps at 10/min, or at minimum correct the comment.\n- Clarify the README about token-bucket vs. leaky-bucket semantics.\n\nI'll leave this open to track that doc/example fix. The library behavior itself is correct and doesn't need changes."}, "id": "call_00_zbu8hYIn6Q0GTHpDYBlh5508", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10094, "output_tokens": 1156, "total_tokens": 11250, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9856}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 737}}}}]}}}
